  <body>
  <div>
      <p>
A 
              <xref outputclass="businessDefinition" keyref="business_definition_lesion">Lesion</xref>
 is a 
              <xref outputclass="class" keyref="class_cell_pathological_abnormality">CELL PATHOLOGICAL ABNORMALITY</xref>.        </p>
      <p>
A 
              <xref outputclass="businessDefinition" keyref="business_definition_lesion">Lesion</xref>
 is an area of abnormal 
              <xref outputclass="class" keyref="class_tissue">TISSUE</xref>.        </p>
      <p>
A 
              <xref outputclass="businessDefinition" keyref="business_definition_lesion">Lesion</xref>
 may be:        </p>
      <ul>
         <li>
            <div>
               <p>benign (not cancer) or</p>
            </div>
         </li>
         <li>
            <div>
               <p>malignant (cancer).</p>
            </div>
         </li>
      </ul>
      <p>
For further information on 
              <xref outputclass="businessDefinition" keyref="business_definition_lesion">Lesions</xref>, see the 
              <xref href="https://www.cancer.gov/dictionary?CdrID=46324"
               scope="external"
               format="html">National Cancer Institute website</xref>.        </p>
  </div>
